Handle Lifetimes <p><code>Handle&lt;T&gt;</code> is a shared reference-counted pointer to an asset. Multiple entities can share the same handle. When all handles are dropped, the asset is eligible for deallocation.</p> <pre><code>fn spawn_enemies(
    mut commands: Commands,
    game_assets: Res&lt;GameAssets&gt;,
) {
    for i in 0..100 {
        commands.spawn((
            Enemy,
            SceneRoot(game_assets.enemy_mesh.clone()),
            Transform::from_xyz(i as f32 * 3.0, 0.0, 0.0),
        ));
    }
}
</code></pre>

docs.text:
Type Behavior <code>Handle&lt;T&gt;</code> Strong reference. Keeps asset loaded. <code>WeakHandle&lt;T&gt;</code> Weak reference. Does not prevent unloading. <code>UntypedHandle</code> Erased type handle. Used for generic asset storage. <pre><code>fn weak_handle_example(mut commands: Commands, asset_server: Res&lt;AssetServer&gt;) {
    let strong: Handle&lt;Image&gt; = asset_server.load("textures/icon.png");
    let weak: WeakHandle&lt;Image&gt; = strong.clone_weak();

    commands.spawn(UiIcon {
        image: strong,
        fallback: weak,
    });
}
</code></pre>

